gomodel:SYNGO_271  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors used synaptosomes derived from vGlut-Venus knockin mice to enrich for glutamatergic presynaptic terminals. Mass spectrometry was performed to detect protein content, which identified PPP3R1. Although this method favors the detection of presynaptic proteins, postsynaptic or extrasynaptic localization of PPP3R1 cannot be excluded with this method.\n\n22/11/2017 Pim\n- Protein listed under accession gi|84794597 in Table S2.. Experimental description: Our S-synaptosome preparation was adapted from two previously published protocols (Hebb & Whittaker, 1958; Huttner et al, 1983). Briefly, forebrains of one or two mice were homogenized in 4 ml of ice-cold homogenization buffer (0.32 M Sucrose, 4 mM HEPES pH 7.4, 1 μM PMSF, 1 μg/ml Aprotinin, 1 μg/ml Leupeptin) using a 5-ml glass-Teflon homogenizer with 12 gentle strokes." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_271" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

